Description: Shoulder sherd of Carian pottery amphora; exterior, from top: set of six concentric circles, wavy horizontal framed by lines and bands, seven rows of short verticals, perhaps in a metopal composition (worn to the left). Hard fired, coarse brown-orange clay with numerous medium-sized inclusions of lime and stone (Munsell 5YR 6/4).
Bibliographic references: Williams & Villing 2006 / Carian Mercenaries at Naukratis? (p.47 fig.2, no.6)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GP.03)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 166, Nau 137, pl. 29i)
